How groups are in RBAC 

AWS EKS (IAM Roles)
Groups are defined in the aws-auth ConfigMap:
bashkubectl edit configmap aws-auth -n kube-system
yamlmapRoles:
  - rolearn: arn:aws:iam::123456789:role/DeveloperRole
    username: developer-{{SessionName}}
    groups:
      - developers          # 👈 this matches your RoleBinding
Any user who assumes that IAM role gets added to the developers group automatically.



Option 3 — Azure AKS (Azure AD)
bash# 1. Create a group in Azure AD
az ad group create --display-name "K8s Developers" --mail-nickname "k8s-developers"

# 2. Get the group Object ID
az ad group show --group "K8s Developers" --query id -o tsv
# e.g. returns: a1b2c3d4-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx

# 3. Add members to the group
az ad group member add --group "K8s Developers" --member-id <user-object-id>



Option 4 — Google GKE (Google Groups)
bash# Enable Google Groups for RBAC when creating/updating cluster
gcloud container clusters update your-cluster \
  --security-group="gke-security-groups@yourdomain.com"
Then create a Google Group (e.g. developers@yourdomain.com) in Google Admin, add your developers to it, and use it in the RoleBinding:
yamlsubjects:
  - kind: Group
    name: developers@yourdomain.com   # Google Group email
    apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io
